# =============================================================================
#  PLUTONIUM SMP — FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================
#
#  HOW TO USE
#  ----------
#  Local development:
#    cp env/frontend.env.example artifacts/plutonium-smp/.env
#    (For local dev, you can leave VITE_API_URL blank — see below)
#
#  Vercel production:
#    Copy each variable into your Vercel project's Environment Variables page.
#    (Project → Settings → Environment Variables)
#
#  IMPORTANT — Vite env variable rules:
#    Only variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to the browser.
#    All other variables are server-only and will be undefined in the frontend.
#
# =============================================================================


# =============================================================================
#  API CONNECTION
# =============================================================================

# The full URL of the API server.
# No trailing slash.
#
# HOW THIS WORKS:
#   - If set:   the frontend calls this URL directly for all API requests.
#   - If blank: Vite's dev server proxies /api → http://localhost:3001
#               (this is the recommended setup for local development).
#
# Local development:    Leave blank (the proxy handles it automatically)
# Vercel production:    https://your-api-project.vercel.app
# Custom domain:        https://api.yourdomain.com
#
# This MUST match the APP_URL set in the API server's environment.
VITE_API_URL=


# =============================================================================
#  BASE PATH
# =============================================================================

# The base URL path the frontend is served from.
#
# Root deployment (most common):  /
# Sub-path deployment example:    /app
#
# Only change this if your hosting puts the site under a sub-path.
# Leave as "/" for Vercel, Netlify, and most other hosts.
BASE_PATH=/
